  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "body": "Currently, the \"download\" attribute is handled as a normal attribute. It would be nice if it could be treated as a boolean value attribute when its value is a boolean. (It's not enough to just make the attribute `HAS_BOOLEAN_VALUE`, since non-boolean values are significant.) For example,\n\n``` javascript\na({href: 'thing', download: true}, 'clickme'); // => <a href=\"thing\" download>clickme</a>\na({href: 'thing', download: 'File.pdf'}, 'clickme'); // => <a href=\"thing\" download=\"File.pdf\">clickme</a>\n```\n\nI think this would better reflect [how the attribute is used](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/a#attr-download) (both as a flag and a value-providing attribute):\n\n> This attribute, if present, indicates that the author intends the hyperlink to be used for downloading a resource...If the attribute has a value, the value will be used as the pre-filled file name in the Save prompt.\n",
